1
00:00:10,833 --> 00:00:12,533
<i> Over here! Someone's here.</i>

2
00:00:12,667 --> 00:00:15,400
<i>Olive? She's still alive!
She's alive!</i>

3
00:00:15,533 --> 00:00:16,733
<i> She's still breathing!</i>

4
00:00:16,867 --> 00:00:17,800
<i> Help me!</i>

5
00:00:17,933 --> 00:00:18,833
<i> Help my daughter!</i>

6
00:00:18,967 --> 00:00:20,333
<i> Olive is my daughter.</i>

7
00:00:20,467 --> 00:00:21,433
<i> She's your sister.</i>

8
00:00:21,567 --> 00:00:23,633
<i>If you can't accept her
as your sister,</i>

9
00:00:23,767 --> 00:00:26,133
<i>please respect her
as a human being.</i>

10
00:00:26,267 --> 00:00:27,233
<i> She's dead now.</i>

11
00:00:27,367 --> 00:00:28,400
<i> I'm sorry, Jade,</i>

12
00:00:28,533 --> 00:00:30,300
<i>but this is the end of my
daughter's connection</i>

13
00:00:30,433 --> 00:00:31,100
<i> with your twin!</i>

14
00:00:31,233 --> 00:00:34,167
<i> I will never stop loving her.</i>

15
00:00:34,333 --> 00:00:39,467
<i> I hope I can go to her wake.</i>

16
00:00:40,067 --> 00:00:41,100
<i> Emma, dear.</i>

17
00:00:41,233 --> 00:00:43,567
<i>I know that you took Mookie to
Olive's burial.</i>

18
00:00:43,700 --> 00:00:44,867
<i> Can you come home now?</i>

19
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:46,067
<i> Thank you...</i>

20
00:00:46,200 --> 00:00:48,067
<i> for my new identity, Jade.</i>

21
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:50,067
<i> No one else will know.</i>

22
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:51,633
<i> It's between you and me.</i>

23
00:00:51,967 --> 00:00:53,000
<i> Olive?</i>

24
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:35,200
Mom.

25
00:01:36,133 --> 00:01:37,100
It's me...

26
00:01:38,267 --> 00:01:39,300
Jade.

27
00:01:46,433 --> 00:01:47,667
That's right, I'm sorry.

28
00:01:50,533 --> 00:01:52,733
I just miss your sister so much.

29
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,167
Me too, Mom.

30
00:01:59,867 --> 00:02:01,133
Can I hug you?

31
00:02:01,533 --> 00:02:04,033
I miss Olive, too.

32
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:30,100
Unfortunately,
Mookie won't be getting any

33
00:02:30,233 --> 00:02:33,400
of Olive's properties.

34
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:36,900
She's not Olive's legal
daughter.

35
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:40,533
She's been using Maria Angela's
birth certificate,

36
00:02:40,667 --> 00:02:42,500
who is already dead.

37
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:46,733
It is the law that the next of
kin will inherit everything.

38
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:48,067
And that's Jade.

39
00:02:50,233 --> 00:02:53,467
I'm so sorry, Emma, Danilo.

40
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:56,800
But don't worry.

41
00:02:57,567 --> 00:02:59,067
I got Mookie,

42
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:00,500
I'll take care of her.

43
00:03:01,267 --> 00:03:03,967
Actually, I can take care
of all of you.

44
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:05,833
Come on...

45
00:03:05,967 --> 00:03:08,000
we're family, remember?

46
00:03:08,633 --> 00:03:09,767
You know what,

47
00:03:09,900 --> 00:03:14,633
I want all of us to live
together.

48
00:03:15,767 --> 00:03:19,633
Actually, I already
bought a property.

49
00:03:19,767 --> 00:03:20,800
Right?

50
00:03:20,967 --> 00:03:22,633
We can all live together!

51
00:03:23,133 --> 00:03:24,400
Wouldn't that be fun?

52
00:03:24,533 --> 00:03:26,067
That's right, Jade.

53
00:03:26,200 --> 00:03:27,767
- That would be fun.
- What?

54
00:03:27,900 --> 00:03:29,000
What do you think?

55
00:03:29,700 --> 00:03:31,100
I'm sorry,

56
00:03:31,233 --> 00:03:33,867
but we don't need
to live with you.

57
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:36,267
We're fine on our own.

58
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:38,900
Come on, Sis!

59
00:03:39,600 --> 00:03:42,633
Please accept my offer.

60
00:03:43,700 --> 00:03:46,367
I have a lot to give.

61
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:49,100
Everything that Mookie needs.

62
00:03:49,233 --> 00:03:50,900
You don't need
to worry about anything.

63
00:03:51,033 --> 00:03:52,533
I can take care of everything.

64
00:03:52,667 --> 00:03:55,200
Jade, I'm sorry.

65
00:03:56,767 --> 00:03:59,000
But Danilo and I can
take care of her.

66
00:03:59,933 --> 00:04:03,700
And if ever we need your help,

67
00:04:04,467 --> 00:04:05,900
we will let you know.

68
00:04:07,033 --> 00:04:08,367
Jade, thank you..

69
00:04:10,700 --> 00:04:12,433
That's too bad.

70
00:04:12,567 --> 00:04:15,400
I thought we could all live
together. Right, Mom?

71
00:04:15,533 --> 00:04:18,267
- That's right.
- Okay, if that's what you want.

72
00:04:20,567 --> 00:04:24,333
Attorney, thank you for coming.

73
00:04:25,700 --> 00:04:27,067
I will walk him out.

74
00:04:28,333 --> 00:04:29,300
Thank you.

75
00:04:29,433 --> 00:04:31,700
- Bye, Sis. Bye.
- Okay, Jade.

76
00:04:31,833 --> 00:04:33,100
Bye, Mom.

77
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:35,167
I'll go ahead.

78
00:04:46,933 --> 00:04:48,133
What's that about?

79
00:04:48,967 --> 00:04:51,200
Your sister just wants
to help out.

80
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:55,167
Mom, I want to live
a peaceful life.

81
00:04:55,300 --> 00:04:58,233
I don't want to remember Olive.
Or see her face!

82
00:04:58,967 --> 00:05:00,167
If you want to live with Jade,

83
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:02,167
I won't stop you.

84
00:05:02,767 --> 00:05:03,867
Emma, come on.

85
00:05:04,867 --> 00:05:06,733
This is not about me.

86
00:05:07,367 --> 00:05:08,700
It's about your daughter.

87
00:05:08,833 --> 00:05:10,200
We have nothing.

88
00:05:10,900 --> 00:05:13,500
We're just staying at somone
else's place.

89
00:05:13,633 --> 00:05:16,400
Mom, we can go back
to our old home.

90
00:05:16,533 --> 00:05:18,933
I will find a job.
I will help Danilo.

91
00:05:19,067 --> 00:05:20,667
We'll get two jobs
if we have to.

92
00:05:21,300 --> 00:05:22,900
Mom, we can get through this.

93
00:05:24,933 --> 00:05:27,767
I'm going to get Mookie
so we can start packing.

94
00:05:37,967 --> 00:05:40,000
Your wife is so stubborn.

95
00:05:40,833 --> 00:05:42,200
What?

96
00:05:42,333 --> 00:05:44,733
Can you provide for Mookie?

97
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:47,633
Mom, to be honest,

98
00:05:49,367 --> 00:05:51,700
our savings are running out.

99
00:05:52,300 --> 00:05:54,433
I'm also in debt.

100
00:05:55,233 --> 00:05:59,700
And I need to pay for the van to
be repaired.

101
00:06:02,967 --> 00:06:06,467
But I have to support
my wife's decision.

102
00:06:09,233 --> 00:06:10,300
How?

103
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,567
Take all their stuff out.

104
00:06:29,700 --> 00:06:32,333
So they won't need to come
inside when they arrive.

105
00:06:32,467 --> 00:06:33,767
Get everything ready, okay?

106
00:06:33,900 --> 00:06:35,867
Don't leave anything behind.

107
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:36,867
Get everything out.

108
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:38,067
Clean it up.

109
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:42,533
Hey.

110
00:06:44,533 --> 00:06:45,633
Hey.

111
00:06:45,767 --> 00:06:46,800
Mrs. Tina.

112
00:06:47,300 --> 00:06:49,233
I'm glad that you're back.

113
00:06:49,933 --> 00:06:51,667
- Yes.
- Edward!

114
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:54,900
Hurry up! Come on!

115
00:06:55,033 --> 00:06:56,733
So they won't need to go inside.

116
00:06:56,867 --> 00:06:58,100
- Why can't we...
- Right here, over here.

117
00:06:58,233 --> 00:06:59,233
Why can't we go inside?

118
00:06:59,367 --> 00:07:00,633
We can't go back?

119
00:07:00,767 --> 00:07:02,467
We still have half a month
left of rent.

120
00:07:06,667 --> 00:07:07,667
Here.

121
00:07:08,900 --> 00:07:10,967
Find a new apartment to rent.

122
00:07:11,100 --> 00:07:14,933
My new tenant has already paid
six months' rent in advance.

123
00:07:15,367 --> 00:07:17,133
And they paid twice the rent,

124
00:07:17,267 --> 00:07:18,267
so you have to go.

125
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:19,467
Mrs. Tina, that's not right.

126
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:20,767
- We paid our rent this month.
- No, you have to go.

127
00:07:20,900 --> 00:07:21,867
Emma, Emma, come on.

128
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:23,767
Nothing will happen even if we
argue with her.

129
00:07:23,900 --> 00:07:25,833
- Come on, let's go.
- Go on. Hurry and go.

130
00:07:25,967 --> 00:07:27,200
Come on. Let's go.

131
00:07:27,967 --> 00:07:29,800
I gave you your money back, so
you should leave.

132
00:07:29,933 --> 00:07:31,500
We'll go, okay?
Come on, let's go.

133
00:07:32,833 --> 00:07:34,933
Mookie, are you okay?

134
00:07:35,467 --> 00:07:37,600
- You seem feverish.
- I'm okay.

135
00:07:37,733 --> 00:07:39,233
I'm gonna find a taxi, Emma.

136
00:07:39,367 --> 00:07:40,433
Okay.

137
00:07:40,567 --> 00:07:41,767
You seem feverish.

138
00:07:44,233 --> 00:07:45,433
Are you cold?

139
00:07:49,267 --> 00:07:51,300
Mookie has a fever, Dan.

140
00:07:51,433 --> 00:07:52,967
- I'm coming, I'm coming.
- She has a fever.

141
00:07:53,100 --> 00:07:54,200
Here, there's a taxi.

142
00:07:56,333 --> 00:07:57,933
Here. Let's go, let's go.

143
00:07:58,933 --> 00:08:00,100
I'm just going to load our
stuff.

144
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:06,100
- Dan! Dan!
- Mookie? Mookie!

145
00:08:06,233 --> 00:08:07,100
Dan, it's Mookie!

146
00:08:07,233 --> 00:08:09,233
Let's bring her to the hospital!
Hurry!

147
00:08:09,367 --> 00:08:10,300
- Dan!
- Okay, let's go..

148
00:08:10,433 --> 00:08:11,667
Mookie! Wait.

149
00:08:12,267 --> 00:08:13,567
Can you bring us to the
hospital?

150
00:08:13,700 --> 00:08:15,433
- Please help us.
- Okay. Okay, Sir.

151
00:08:15,567 --> 00:08:16,800
Dan, hurry!

152
00:08:16,933 --> 00:08:18,433
Mookie! Dear!

153
00:08:22,067 --> 00:08:23,067
Emma, the door.

154
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:28,467
Okay, Sir.
To the hospital, please.

155
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:30,300
- Okay.
- Hurry up!

156
00:08:44,833 --> 00:08:45,833
Hello, Ma'am?

157
00:08:46,533 --> 00:08:48,233
Please check your cash wallet.

158
00:08:48,767 --> 00:08:52,067
I have already transferred the
remaining six months' rent.

159
00:08:52,633 --> 00:08:53,667
Yes, Ma'am.

160
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:56,433
Thank you. Thank you so much.

161
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:58,333
Oh, you will surely stay
a long time

162
00:08:58,467 --> 00:08:59,900
in my apartment.

163
00:09:00,033 --> 00:09:01,633
<i> Thank you so much.</i>

164
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:09,433
Wherever you go, Emma,

165
00:09:10,567 --> 00:09:15,100
I will make sure you'll end up
with me.

166
00:09:16,867 --> 00:09:18,433
All of you.

167
00:09:20,767 --> 00:09:22,000
My daughter has pneumonia.

168
00:09:23,233 --> 00:09:24,800
Bactrerial pnuemonia.

169
00:09:24,933 --> 00:09:26,300
Looks like she's been having
a hard time breathing

170
00:09:26,433 --> 00:09:27,700
for days now.

171
00:09:27,867 --> 00:09:28,633
What?

172
00:09:29,700 --> 00:09:32,133
Why didn't she tell us?

173
00:09:32,267 --> 00:09:34,367
She probably didn't want us
to worry.

174
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:36,000
Excuse me, I have to go.

175
00:09:36,133 --> 00:09:38,167
I have other patients
to look at.

176
00:09:38,300 --> 00:09:39,467
Thank you, Doctor.

177
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:47,133
Sis, chill, okay?

178
00:09:47,267 --> 00:09:49,467
I'm here to help.

179
00:09:51,167 --> 00:09:52,567
We can handle this, Jade.

180
00:09:53,700 --> 00:09:54,867
Are you sure?

181
00:09:55,967 --> 00:09:58,767
What if Mookie's condition
worsens?

182
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:02,200
How are you going to pay
the hospital bills?

183
00:10:02,367 --> 00:10:03,967
How are you going
to buy her medicine?

184
00:10:05,067 --> 00:10:08,767
Didn't you say that you have no
job right now?

185
00:10:08,900 --> 00:10:10,567
And Danilo's pay
has been delayed

186
00:10:10,700 --> 00:10:12,067
for a couple of months now.

187
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:16,367
He also has to take care
of the van's repairs.

188
00:10:17,767 --> 00:10:19,067
Sis, sorry.

189
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:22,333
I'm not trying to meddle
in your affairs.

190
00:10:22,467 --> 00:10:25,700
But Mom told me about your
situation right now,

191
00:10:25,833 --> 00:10:29,367
and I just want to help
my niece.

192
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:32,200
I know that she has
a weak immune system.

193
00:10:32,333 --> 00:10:33,933
What if she suffers?

194
00:10:34,100 --> 00:10:35,833
Would you let that happen?

195
00:10:41,867 --> 00:10:45,000
I understand if you don't want
my help.

196
00:10:46,033 --> 00:10:48,267
I won't force myself on you.

197
00:11:09,300 --> 00:11:10,200
Jade?

198
00:11:15,167 --> 00:11:15,900
Yes?

199
00:11:26,267 --> 00:11:27,733
<i> After two weeks.</i>

200
00:11:27,867 --> 00:11:31,733
Welcome! Welcome! Come in, come
in!

201
00:11:31,867 --> 00:11:33,333
- Wow!
- Feel at home.

202
00:11:33,467 --> 00:11:37,700
Welcome to our new home!

203
00:11:37,833 --> 00:11:38,467
It's so stylish!

204
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:39,400
Welcome!

205
00:11:39,833 --> 00:11:41,233
It's so stylish!

206
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:46,100
- Oh, Danilo!
- Yes, Jade?

207
00:11:46,233 --> 00:11:47,733
By the way,
I have some good news for you.

208
00:11:47,867 --> 00:11:51,833
Don't worry about
the van's damage.

209
00:11:51,967 --> 00:11:54,900
- I already took care of it.
- Oh my, that's embarrassing.

210
00:11:55,033 --> 00:11:58,667
Thank you, but I'll pay you
back in installments.

211
00:11:58,800 --> 00:11:59,933
Is that okay?

212
00:12:00,067 --> 00:12:01,867
What are you talking about?
There's no need to do that.

213
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:04,333
But if you insist, that's fine.

214
00:12:04,467 --> 00:12:05,667
I can offer you a job.

215
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:06,833
If you want,

216
00:12:06,967 --> 00:12:10,433
you can work as my driver
once I start working

217
00:12:10,567 --> 00:12:11,567
at Artemis Pharmacy.

218
00:12:11,700 --> 00:12:15,133
Really? That sounds good!
I'll take the job. Okay.

219
00:12:16,567 --> 00:12:19,667
Dan, why don't we just pay Jade
the money?

220
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:21,233
So it's not embarrassing.

221
00:12:21,367 --> 00:12:23,867
That way, you wouldn't
have to resign from your job.

222
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:26,033
But, Emma, what are you talking
about?

223
00:12:26,167 --> 00:12:28,333
You should agree to it,
don't you like that?

224
00:12:28,467 --> 00:12:30,400
Danilo won't have to go far.

225
00:12:30,533 --> 00:12:32,700
He doesn't need to drive out
to the province.

226
00:12:32,833 --> 00:12:34,433
- That's right, Emma.
- Right.

227
00:12:35,567 --> 00:12:37,000
Oh, by the way,

228
00:12:37,133 --> 00:12:39,000
I have a surprise for all
of you.

229
00:12:39,133 --> 00:12:41,867
Loida, can you give them their
gifts?

230
00:12:42,533 --> 00:12:43,300
Gift?

231
00:12:43,433 --> 00:12:44,900
I have a welcome gift for all
of you.

232
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:45,800
Wow!

233
00:12:45,933 --> 00:12:48,133
Of course, a new home, remember?

234
00:12:49,467 --> 00:12:51,167
We have a gift too?
Thank you so much.

235
00:12:51,300 --> 00:12:52,967
You're extraordinary, Jade.

236
00:12:53,100 --> 00:12:55,267
Miss Generosity of the year!

237
00:12:58,133 --> 00:12:59,500
Enjoy!

238
00:13:01,367 --> 00:13:02,167
Wow!

239
00:13:03,333 --> 00:13:04,867
- It's gorgeous!
- This is so nice!

240
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:06,633
It's a lot.

241
00:13:06,767 --> 00:13:11,700
Clothes, and more boxed stuff.

242
00:13:11,833 --> 00:13:13,367
What is this?

243
00:13:14,700 --> 00:13:16,667
Jade, thank you so much.

244
00:13:20,133 --> 00:13:20,800
Sweetie!

245
00:13:21,933 --> 00:13:22,767
It's jewelry.

246
00:13:23,033 --> 00:13:25,100
It's the first time I have
something like this.

247
00:13:25,233 --> 00:13:27,000
- Thank you so much.
- You're welcome.

248
00:13:27,133 --> 00:13:29,633
Danilo, this is for you.

249
00:13:29,767 --> 00:13:30,933
Oh my, thank you.

250
00:13:31,067 --> 00:13:32,567
I hope you like it.

251
00:13:32,700 --> 00:13:34,100
I chose that for you.

252
00:13:34,233 --> 00:13:36,433
Auntie Jade, thank you.

253
00:13:36,567 --> 00:13:39,267
- You're welcome, baby girl!
- Thank you, Auntie.

254
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:41,400
That's the latest model.

255
00:13:41,967 --> 00:13:44,500
Look, Mom, I have
a new cellphone!

256
00:13:56,233 --> 00:13:59,000
<i>Welcome to your new hell, Emma.</i>

257
00:13:59,133 --> 00:14:02,067
<i>I won't just take Mookie
from you.</i>

258
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:05,200
<i>I will take everyone
that you love.</i>

259
00:14:11,567 --> 00:14:12,600
Thank you.

260
00:14:23,467 --> 00:14:25,133
That's easier.

261
00:14:25,267 --> 00:14:26,200
Like that?

262
00:14:27,633 --> 00:14:28,567
Like this?

263
00:14:30,333 --> 00:14:31,800
Okay, have fun.

264
00:14:34,733 --> 00:14:37,367
Emma, look at our daughter.

265
00:14:37,500 --> 00:14:39,333
She's dancing.

266
00:14:39,467 --> 00:14:41,800
She's so happy. Right?

267
00:14:41,933 --> 00:14:43,133
Because of Jade.

268
00:14:45,033 --> 00:14:46,767
Why? Do you have a problem
with Jade?

269
00:14:48,733 --> 00:14:51,100
No, I don't have a problem
with her. I'm just sad.

270
00:14:52,967 --> 00:14:57,433
Because we can't give Mookie
all those things

271
00:14:57,567 --> 00:14:59,067
that make her happy.

272
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:02,067
Like this nice house.

273
00:15:02,233 --> 00:15:04,300
And abundant food.

274
00:15:04,433 --> 00:15:06,967
Look at how happy
all of them are.

275
00:15:07,100 --> 00:15:10,767
She made all of them happy,
not just Mookie.

276
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:14,933
Look at Mom.

277
00:15:15,067 --> 00:15:18,967
Look at how fancy that jewelry
Jade gave her is.

278
00:15:19,100 --> 00:15:21,000
She's so happy.

279
00:15:23,900 --> 00:15:25,333
And you...

280
00:15:25,467 --> 00:15:27,300
What about me?

281
00:15:27,433 --> 00:15:29,867
Look at how happy you are.

282
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:34,500
All because Jade took care
of all your debts.

283
00:15:34,667 --> 00:15:37,000
And she gave you a job.

284
00:15:41,233 --> 00:15:45,900
You're just jealous.

285
00:15:46,033 --> 00:15:46,900
No, I'm not.

286
00:15:47,033 --> 00:15:49,200
Don't be jealous.
Come on, let's dance.

287
00:15:49,333 --> 00:15:50,300
Dance?

288
00:15:50,433 --> 00:15:51,400
- What are you doing?
- Come on, let's dance.

289
00:15:51,533 --> 00:15:53,100
Dan, stop it, it's embarrassing.

290
00:15:53,233 --> 00:15:54,433
Come on, like this.
Just do what they do.

291
00:15:54,567 --> 00:15:54,867
It's embarrassing.

292
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:55,500
Like this.

293
00:15:55,633 --> 00:15:56,767
See?

294
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:00,367
- Oh, don't. Maybe you...
- What's with you?

295
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:01,600
What's embarrassing
about this?

296
00:16:01,733 --> 00:16:04,000
Is this their first time
seeing a married couple dance?

297
00:16:04,133 --> 00:16:05,900
Stop it, you're so annoying.

298
00:16:06,033 --> 00:16:07,267
We're just dancing.

299
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:08,633
Then we'll hug, like this.

300
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:09,567
Right?

301
00:16:09,700 --> 00:16:11,433
Whatever.

302
00:16:11,567 --> 00:16:12,700
What...

303
00:16:12,833 --> 00:16:14,333
You guys are so sweet!

304
00:16:14,467 --> 00:16:16,400
- Oh, no.
- Hey. Jade.

305
00:16:16,533 --> 00:16:17,133
Have some food.

306
00:16:17,267 --> 00:16:17,667
Okay.

307
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:18,267
Can I have some?

308
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:18,933
Okay.

309
00:16:19,067 --> 00:16:21,900
Go on, dance.

310
00:16:24,733 --> 00:16:25,667
You want some chicken?

311
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:27,000
I'll just have this for now.

312
00:16:27,133 --> 00:16:28,733
You told me earlier
you wanted chicken.

313
00:16:34,467 --> 00:16:36,167
<i> Go ahead, Emma.</i>

314
00:16:36,300 --> 00:16:39,733
<i>Enjoy your happy moments
while you still can.</i>

315
00:16:39,867 --> 00:16:42,667
<i> It won't last.</i>

316
00:17:36,800 --> 00:17:38,000
I'm sorry, did I startle you?

317
00:17:39,100 --> 00:17:43,333
I want to thank you
for letting us live here.

318
00:17:44,133 --> 00:17:46,667
I dreamt of this
for a long time.

319
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:48,967
To be with all my children.

320
00:17:50,067 --> 00:17:51,367
Too bad...

321
00:17:52,467 --> 00:17:53,967
Olive is gone now.

322
00:17:56,533 --> 00:17:57,367
But you know what...

323
00:17:58,467 --> 00:18:00,000
I will make it up to you, Jade.

324
00:18:01,867 --> 00:18:03,267
I will take care of you.

325
00:18:04,667 --> 00:18:10,600
I will do anything
to make you feel my love.

326
00:18:10,733 --> 00:18:13,800
And I will double it, for Olive.

327
00:18:13,933 --> 00:18:15,567
To make it up to her.

328
00:18:17,267 --> 00:18:18,700
Thank you, sweetie.

329
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:35,200
It's okay, Mom.

330
00:18:35,333 --> 00:18:37,933
It's all in the past now.

331
00:18:38,067 --> 00:18:39,567
Let's not dwell on it.

332
00:18:40,567 --> 00:18:42,967
We'll start anew.

333
00:18:44,100 --> 00:18:45,233
Thank you.

334
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:47,700
It's okay, Mom.

335
00:18:47,833 --> 00:18:49,967
Go hang out with your friends.

336
00:18:50,100 --> 00:18:51,467
Right, they're so happy.

337
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:53,467
They're enjoying themselves.

338
00:18:53,600 --> 00:18:54,667
It's the first time
for all of us.

339
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:57,133
It's all because of you.

340
00:18:57,300 --> 00:18:59,567
- Come hang out with us, okay?
- Okay, I will.

341
00:19:29,267 --> 00:19:30,767
Emma, dear!

342
00:19:30,900 --> 00:19:35,367
Come with me to the market,
I want to cook for Jade.

343
00:19:35,500 --> 00:19:37,467
Did you forget that we have
to go somewhere today?

344
00:19:37,600 --> 00:19:40,100
We're supposed to inquire
at Marcela Agoncillo?

345
00:19:40,233 --> 00:19:41,400
For Mookie.

346
00:19:41,533 --> 00:19:43,633
Oh my, I'm sorry,
I forgot bout that.

347
00:19:43,767 --> 00:19:44,800
But...

348
00:19:44,933 --> 00:19:45,933
you can take care of
that yourself.

349
00:19:46,067 --> 00:19:47,500
Go on without me, okay?

350
00:19:47,633 --> 00:19:48,733
Mom.

351
00:19:48,867 --> 00:19:50,633
Mom, be honest with me.

352
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:55,500
You didn't want to come
here for Mookie, right?

353
00:19:55,633 --> 00:19:57,200
It's because of Jade.

354
00:19:57,333 --> 00:19:58,900
You want to be with her.

355
00:20:02,133 --> 00:20:04,000
Okay, you're right.

356
00:20:05,400 --> 00:20:09,933
Emma, I want to make it up
to your sister. I'm sorry.

357
00:20:10,067 --> 00:20:11,767
The problem is that
you're forgetting

358
00:20:11,900 --> 00:20:14,400
that you still have another
child and a grandchild.

359
00:20:15,800 --> 00:20:17,467
That's not true.

360
00:20:17,600 --> 00:20:20,100
The moment you find out
about them,

361
00:20:21,100 --> 00:20:22,400
you think of no one else
but them.

362
00:20:26,833 --> 00:20:30,000
Emma, don't think like that.

363
00:20:30,133 --> 00:20:31,033
Emma!

364
00:20:31,833 --> 00:20:33,700
Hey, that's not true!

365
00:20:36,900 --> 00:20:38,033
Mom!

366
00:20:38,167 --> 00:20:38,633
Oh...

367
00:20:39,733 --> 00:20:40,500
Jade.

368
00:20:41,500 --> 00:20:43,467
So Emma is getting jealous.

369
00:20:44,700 --> 00:20:46,300
To be honest,

370
00:20:46,433 --> 00:20:50,600
I think it's a bit petty.

371
00:20:50,733 --> 00:20:58,833
Seriously, though, she might
take this jealousy too hard.

372
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:01,833
Sorry, dear.

373
00:21:01,967 --> 00:21:04,200
So you overheard
our conversation.

374
00:21:05,100 --> 00:21:06,967
I'm sorry about that.

375
00:21:07,100 --> 00:21:10,233
But I hope she won't take this
too hard.

376
00:21:11,600 --> 00:21:12,933
But how?

377
00:21:13,067 --> 00:21:15,367
We all live together.

378
00:21:15,500 --> 00:21:17,300
That's likely to happen.

379
00:21:17,433 --> 00:21:20,433
Especially when
she can see us together.

380
00:21:20,567 --> 00:21:23,367
She might end up resenting me.

381
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:25,100
That sounds like trouble.

382
00:21:26,867 --> 00:21:27,800
I'm sorry.

383
00:21:28,667 --> 00:21:31,467
I have a brilliant idea, Mom.

384
00:21:31,600 --> 00:21:36,133
What about going on a vacation

385
00:21:36,700 --> 00:21:39,033
to give Emma some time to think?

386
00:21:39,567 --> 00:21:44,800
It will also allow me
to get close to her.

387
00:21:45,533 --> 00:21:47,700
What do you think, Mom?

388
00:21:47,833 --> 00:21:50,600
All expenses paid.

389
00:21:54,467 --> 00:21:55,433
What?

390
00:21:56,967 --> 00:21:58,467
You know what...

391
00:21:58,600 --> 00:22:01,367
you have a point there.

392
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:02,400
Because...

393
00:22:03,367 --> 00:22:08,700
If Emma's jealousy gets worse,
she might end up resenting you.

394
00:22:10,700 --> 00:22:11,700
So what do you think?

395
00:22:11,833 --> 00:22:15,100
Have you thought
of a place to visit?

396
00:22:17,400 --> 00:22:19,067
I can go to Cebu,

397
00:22:19,200 --> 00:22:21,867
it's been a while since
I visited my family there.

398
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:25,033
I miss them.

399
00:22:25,167 --> 00:22:26,500
Prefect!

400
00:22:26,633 --> 00:22:30,400
You can take a vacation there,
I'll take care of everything.

401
00:22:30,533 --> 00:22:33,733
You can take Wiro and Kutsy
with you for company.

402
00:22:33,867 --> 00:22:36,500
- Really?
- Not only that...

403
00:22:36,633 --> 00:22:40,467
I can give you more allowance.

404
00:22:40,600 --> 00:22:41,567
You want that?

405
00:22:45,167 --> 00:22:48,800
I don't need
to take my friends with me.

406
00:22:48,967 --> 00:22:50,300
I can go by myself.

407
00:22:51,400 --> 00:22:52,567
But you're right.

408
00:22:52,700 --> 00:22:55,000
It will be fun
to bring them along.

409
00:22:55,133 --> 00:22:55,933
Okay, Mom.

410
00:22:56,067 --> 00:22:57,467
I'll take care of everything,
okay?

411
00:23:03,467 --> 00:23:04,633
Oh, Dan.

412
00:23:04,767 --> 00:23:06,367
Come, sit here.

413
00:23:06,500 --> 00:23:08,700
You're the head of the family.

414
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:17,567
- There! Let's eat!
- You don't need to do all this.

415
00:23:17,700 --> 00:23:19,500
What are you talking about?

416
00:23:19,633 --> 00:23:21,600
This is just take-out food.

417
00:23:21,767 --> 00:23:24,600
I want to serve my family.

418
00:23:24,733 --> 00:23:27,033
Good morning, Sis!

419
00:23:27,167 --> 00:23:28,300
Good morning!

420
00:23:28,433 --> 00:23:30,300
You're here right on time.

421
00:23:30,433 --> 00:23:32,433
Come sit down,
it's time for breakfast.

422
00:23:32,567 --> 00:23:34,033
Go ahead, eat. Come, eat!

423
00:23:35,867 --> 00:23:38,167
Come eat. Go, baby girl!

424
00:23:38,300 --> 00:23:39,767
Let's eat.

425
00:23:43,700 --> 00:23:45,533
Let's eat.

426
00:23:46,467 --> 00:23:49,233
Danilo, are you doing
something later today?

427
00:23:49,367 --> 00:23:51,867
- Thank you, Mom.
- We can buy your polo shirts,

428
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:56,500
so you can start driving for me.

429
00:23:56,667 --> 00:23:57,800
Okay.

430
00:23:57,933 --> 00:24:00,700
Baby girl, don't you have a
doctor's appointment today?

431
00:24:00,833 --> 00:24:02,633
You want me to come with you?

432
00:24:02,767 --> 00:24:04,433
Jade.

433
00:24:04,567 --> 00:24:08,400
Is it okay if I go with
Danilo to get his shirts?

434
00:24:08,533 --> 00:24:13,000
And I can take Mookie
to her appointment.

435
00:24:13,133 --> 00:24:17,300
I'm his wife and Mookie's mom,
remember?

436
00:24:17,433 --> 00:24:19,233
Of course, Sis!

437
00:24:19,367 --> 00:24:22,467
I'm sorry about that,
I'm just a bit excited.

438
00:24:22,600 --> 00:24:23,800
Okay.

439
00:24:23,933 --> 00:24:25,833
Enjoy your breakfast, fam.

440
00:24:25,967 --> 00:24:27,633
I'll just have my coffee here.

441
00:24:33,567 --> 00:24:34,900
Emma.

442
00:24:35,033 --> 00:24:37,767
Why are you being rude
to your sister?

443
00:24:37,900 --> 00:24:41,300
She's just doing us a favor.

444
00:24:41,433 --> 00:24:43,433
I'm sorry,
I'm still a bit tired.

445
00:24:44,567 --> 00:24:46,500
Where's Mom at?

446
00:24:46,633 --> 00:24:48,633
Is she still sleeping?

447
00:24:48,767 --> 00:24:51,533
She didn't tell you?

448
00:24:51,667 --> 00:24:54,467
Auntie Jade knows where she is.

449
00:25:06,600 --> 00:25:09,400
Jade, did Mom tell you
she's leaving?

450
00:25:09,867 --> 00:25:10,933
Or did you make her go?

451
00:25:11,933 --> 00:25:13,733
I sent her on vacation.

452
00:25:13,867 --> 00:25:16,333
Because the two of you are
not getting along, right?

453
00:25:16,467 --> 00:25:19,000
So I suggested she go on
vacation to give you time

454
00:25:19,133 --> 00:25:20,433
to miss her.

455
00:25:20,567 --> 00:25:24,833
And for me to be able to start
with my plans with you.

456
00:25:30,967 --> 00:25:34,000
I got you a slot at
St. Margaret Academy!

457
00:25:34,133 --> 00:25:34,867
Here!

458
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:35,900
Wow!

459
00:25:36,067 --> 00:25:36,967
Let me see that.

460
00:25:38,300 --> 00:25:39,367
Why are you making decisions
for her?

461
00:25:39,500 --> 00:25:40,833
The Ethereon tablets, Ma'am,

462
00:25:40,967 --> 00:25:43,267
cause hot temper
and irritability.

463
00:25:43,400 --> 00:25:46,200
And Auroxen solution
causes paranoia.

464
00:25:46,333 --> 00:25:48,967
And Lunavaxil patches
cause hallucinations.

465
00:25:49,100 --> 00:25:51,000
The effects is fast.

466
00:25:52,867 --> 00:25:54,200
That's right, Olive.

467
00:25:54,333 --> 00:25:56,733
Don't be in such a hurry.

468
00:25:56,867 --> 00:26:00,200
Slowly drive Emma insane.

469
00:26:00,333 --> 00:26:04,000
Your mom, Emma,
is she a super mom?

470
00:26:04,133 --> 00:26:06,800
Is she better than Olive?

471
00:26:06,933 --> 00:26:08,833
She's way better than Mommy.

472
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:09,867
No!

473
00:26:12,033 --> 00:26:12,967
Auntie?
